quizzes.question:
Fill in the blanks to test both conditions in the following if statement.
[!raw!]
int age = 23;
int money = 4;
if (age > 21 {0} money > 500) {
 cout << "welcome" << endl;
}

quizzes.textContent:
[h1]The AND Operator [/h1]

[b]For example:[/b] [code format="cpp" codeId="213"]int age = 20;
if (age > 16 [b]&&[/b] age < 60) {
  cout << "Accepted!" << endl;
}

// Outputs "Accepted"[/code]
In the example above, the logical AND operator was used to combine both expressions. 
[note]The expression in the if statement evaluates to [b]true [/b]only if both expressions are [b]true[/b].[/note]

[h1]The AND Operator[/h1]

Within a single if statement, logical operators can be used to combine [b]multiple [/b]conditions. [code format="cpp" codeId="214"]int age = 20;
int grade = 80;

if (age > 16 [b]&&[/b] age < 60 [b]&&[/b] grade > 50) {
  cout << "Accepted!" << endl;
}[/code]
[note]The entire expression evaluates to [b]true [/b]only if all of the conditions are [b]true[/b].[/note]

